com.cyc.base.inference

Interface InferenceParameterSetter

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    InferenceParameters
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultInferenceParameters, Query, SpecifiedInferenceParameters

    public interface InferenceParameterSetter
    An interface defining the setters of Cyc inference parameters. Implementing classes allow the various parameters that govern how Cyc performs inference to be specified.

    By convention, the setter methods return the object itself, to allow method calls to be chained.

      • setContinuable

        InferenceParameterSetter setContinuable(boolean b)
        Specify whether inferences should be continuable. Continuable inferences are used e.g. when a maximum number of answers has been specified. The inference will be suspended after an initial batch of answers has been found, and continuing it may then yield the next batch.
        Parameters:
        b -

      • setInferenceMode

        InferenceParameterSetter setInferenceMode(InferenceMode mode)
        Set the inference mode. Inference modes are meant to be intuitive measures of how hard Cyc should work to answer a query. Setting the inference mode sets various other low-level parameters to appropriate values for that mode, but explictly setting values for such parameters overrides values set by the mode.
        Parameters:
        mode -
        Returns:
        this object.

      • setMaxNumber

        InferenceParameterSetter setMaxNumber(Integer max)
        Set the max number value. Setting this parameter to some number licenses Cyc to stop work on an inference once it has found at least that many answers.

        A value of null means the inference will continue until it exhausts or some other limit is reached.

        Parameters:
        max -
        Returns:
        this object.

      • setMaxTime

        InferenceParameterSetter setMaxTime(Integer max)
        Set the max time value (in seconds). Setting this parameter to some number licenses Cyc to stop work on an inference once it has been working on it for at least that many seconds.

        A value of null means the inference will continue until it exhausts or some other limit is reached.

        Parameters:
        max -
        Returns:
        this object.
